1
00:00:01,251 --> 00:00:03,378
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

2
00:00:19,353 --> 00:00:21,772
RADIO: Viking, North Utsire,
South Utsire,

3
00:00:21,855 --> 00:00:25,067
wind south west,
rain at times, good.

4
00:00:30,155 --> 00:00:33,575
CLARA: "Waste no more time
arguing about what a good man should be.

5
00:00:33,784 --> 00:00:36,495
"Be one."”
Marcus Aurelius.

6
00:00:46,129 --> 00:00:49,174
-Have you been running?
-Are you okay?

7
00:00:49,299 --> 00:00:51,510
There was a call for you
at the office.

8
00:00:52,135 --> 00:00:53,512
From your...doctor.

9
00:00:55,681 --> 00:00:57,975
Did he leave an address?

10
00:01:24,418 --> 00:01:26,003
(HORN HONKING)

11
00:01:41,184 --> 00:01:43,186
Draught.

12
00:01:45,689 --> 00:01:50,068
Fancy a week in Ancient Mesopotamia,
followed by future Mars?

13
00:01:50,193 --> 00:01:53,196
-Will there be cocktails?
-On the Moon.

14
00:01:53,405 --> 00:01:56,074
The Moon'll do.

15
00:01:56,575 --> 00:01:59,119
(BOTH LAUGH JOYOUSLY)

16
00:02:01,705 --> 00:02:03,915
How's the new job? Teach anything good?

17
00:02:03,999 --> 00:02:05,292
No. Learn anything?

18
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:07,502
Not a thing.

19
00:02:07,586 --> 00:02:11,256
- (CLANK)
-(LOUD WHIRRING)

20
00:02:11,381 --> 00:02:14,134
-What's happening?
-Whoa, whoa. We're taking off.

21
00:02:14,217 --> 00:02:15,385
But the engines aren't going.

22
00:02:18,388 --> 00:02:20,140
PILOT OVER RADIO:
Wait for it to level, Greyhound leader.

23
00:02:20,223 --> 00:02:22,392
Blue Eagle is
airborne and ready to receive.

24
00:02:23,727 --> 00:02:25,520
We're on our way.

25
00:02:32,694 --> 00:02:35,822
-(WHOOSHING)
-(PHONE BEEPS)

26
00:02:35,906 --> 00:02:38,575
0SGOOD: Hello?
Kate Stewart's phone. Oh, hold on.

27
00:02:38,742 --> 00:02:41,078
Excuse me! Sorry.

28
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:45,207
-Ma'am! Ma'am!
-The ravens are looking a bit sluggish.

29
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:47,668
-Tell Malcolm we need new batteries.
-It's him.

30
00:02:47,751 --> 00:02:51,505
Sorry. It's your personal phone,
but I recognised the ringtone.

31
00:02:51,588 --> 00:02:53,715
-(BREATHLESS) It's him, isn't it?
-Inhaler.

32
00:02:53,799 --> 00:02:56,009
Doctor, hello.
We found the Tardis in a field.

33
00:02:56,093 --> 00:02:58,970
-I'm having it brought in.
-No kidding!

34
00:03:00,138 --> 00:03:02,015
Where are you?

35
00:03:05,769 --> 00:03:07,354
Oh, my God.

36
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:11,942
Oh, Doctor, I'm so sorry.
We had no idea you were still in there.

37
00:03:13,193 --> 00:03:14,861
Come on.

38
00:03:14,945 --> 00:03:17,948
PILOT: Roger. New heading, 2-7-0.
Changing course.

39
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:20,242
-(SCREAMS)
-Doctor?

40
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:22,661
Clara!

41
00:03:22,786 --> 00:03:24,788
-Doctor, can you hear me?
-Ow!

42
00:03:24,913 --> 00:03:26,998
I don't think he can hear me.

43
00:03:27,124 --> 00:03:29,918
(YELLS) Next time,
would it kill you to knock?

44
00:03:30,001 --> 00:03:32,796
I'm having you taken directly
to the scene.

45
00:03:37,801 --> 00:03:39,553
Doctor, hello. Are you okay?

46
00:03:40,637 --> 00:03:43,181
I'm just going to pop you on hold.

47
00:03:43,306 --> 00:03:45,767
-Doctor?
-(GASPS) Doctor!

48
00:03:47,269 --> 00:03:49,229
(YELLING)

49
00:04:17,299 --> 00:04:19,134
GUARD: Attention!

50
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:23,346
-Why am I saluting?
-Doctor.

51
00:04:23,472 --> 00:04:25,682
As Chief Scientific Officer,
may I extend

52
00:04:25,807 --> 00:04:27,893
the official apologies of UNIT...

53
00:04:28,018 --> 00:04:30,729
Kate Lethbridge-Stewart,
a word to the wise.

54
00:04:30,854 --> 00:04:33,190
As I'm sure your father
would have told you,

55
00:04:33,315 --> 00:04:36,193
I don't like being picked up.

56
00:04:36,318 --> 00:04:38,361
That probably sounded better
in his head.

57
00:04:38,487 --> 00:04:41,364
I'm acting on instructions
direct from the throne.

58
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:46,036
Sealed orders from Her Majesty
Queen Elizabeth the First.

59
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:49,706
The Queen? The First?

60
00:04:49,831 --> 00:04:52,751
-Sorry, Elizabeth the First?
-Her credentials are inside.

61
00:04:54,211 --> 00:04:56,087
No, inside.

62
00:04:58,215 --> 00:04:59,257
Nice scarf.

63
00:05:00,926 --> 00:05:03,595
-What's our cover story for this?
-Um, Derren Brown.

64
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:06,389
-Again?
-Oh, we sent him flowers.

65
00:05:06,515 --> 00:05:10,894
GUARD: Attention! Right, I want
a secure perimeter around the gallery.

66
00:05:11,728 --> 00:05:14,231
Did you know her? Elizabeth the First?

67
00:05:14,356 --> 00:05:16,900
-Unified Intelligence Task Force.
-Sorry?

68
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:19,361
This lot. UNIT. They investigate
alien stuff. Anything alien.

69
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:21,112
-What, like you?
-I work for them.

70
00:05:21,238 --> 00:05:23,240
You have a job?

71
00:05:23,365 --> 00:05:25,242
Why shouldn't I have a job?
I'd be brilliant at having a job.

72
00:05:25,408 --> 00:05:28,495
-You don't have a job.
-I do. This is my job. I'm doing it now.

73
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:30,747
-You never have a job.
-I do! I do.

74
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:36,670
KATE: Elizabeth's credentials, Doctor.

75
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:38,672
But...

76
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:40,549
But that's not possible.

77
00:05:40,799 --> 00:05:42,509
No more.

78
00:05:42,592 --> 00:05:44,261
"No more."

79
00:05:44,386 --> 00:05:46,847
-That's the title.
-I know the title.

80
00:05:46,930 --> 00:05:48,515
Also known as Gallifrey Falls.

81
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:51,226
This painting doesn't belong here.
Not in this time or place.

82
00:05:51,309 --> 00:05:53,061
CLARA: Obviously.

83
00:05:53,895 --> 00:05:57,023
It's the fall of Arcadia,
Gallifrey's second city.

84
00:05:57,107 --> 00:05:59,609
But how is it doing that?
How is that possible?

85
00:06:01,403 --> 00:06:03,488
It's an oil painting...

86
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:07,284
...in 3D.

87
00:06:08,451 --> 00:06:10,203
DOCTOR: Time Lord art.

88
00:06:10,287 --> 00:06:13,415
Bigger on the inside.
A slice of real time,

89
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:15,625
frozen.

90
00:06:16,626 --> 00:06:19,379
KATE: Elizabeth told us
where to find it,

91
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:21,256
and its significance.

92
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:27,137
-You okay?
-He was there.

93
00:06:27,971 --> 00:06:29,639
-Who was?
-Me.

94
00:06:32,142 --> 00:06:35,228
The other me.
The one I don't talk about.

95
00:06:35,312 --> 00:06:37,898
I don't understand.

96
00:06:37,981 --> 00:06:40,942
I've had many faces. Many lives.

97
00:06:41,026 --> 00:06:44,321
I don't admit to all of them.
There's one life I've tried

98
00:06:44,446 --> 00:06:46,406
very hard to forget.

99
00:06:46,489 --> 00:06:47,532
WHISPER: No more...

100
00:06:47,657 --> 00:06:51,286
He was the Doctor
who fought in the Time War,

101
00:06:51,369 --> 00:06:54,414
and that was the day he did it.
The day I did it.

102
00:06:54,497 --> 00:06:56,666
The day he killed them all.

103
00:06:57,792 --> 00:07:00,503
The last day of the Time War,

104
00:07:00,629 --> 00:07:05,133
the war to end all wars
between my people and the Daleks.

105
00:07:05,216 --> 00:07:07,260
And in that battle, there was a man

106
00:07:07,344 --> 00:07:10,055
with more blood on his hands
than any other.

107
00:07:10,180 --> 00:07:13,808
A man who would commit a crime
that would silence the universe.

108
00:07:13,892 --> 00:07:16,686
And that man was me.

109
00:07:27,656 --> 00:07:29,741
(PANICKED SCREAMING)

110
00:08:12,909 --> 00:08:14,536
DALEK: Exterminate.

111
00:08:16,955 --> 00:08:20,792
Exterminate. Exterminate.

112
00:08:26,881 --> 00:08:30,260
A message for the High Council.
Priority Omega.

113
00:08:30,385 --> 00:08:34,764
Arcadia has fallen.
I repeat, Arcadia has fallen.

114
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:37,308
(TRANSMITTER BLEEPS)

115
00:08:42,939 --> 00:08:47,902
Soldier, I'm going to need your gun.

116
00:08:55,118 --> 00:08:57,120
(SCREAMING)

117
00:08:59,539 --> 00:09:03,668
Exterminate. Exterminate.

118
00:09:05,128 --> 00:09:07,589
Exterminate.

119
00:09:09,507 --> 00:09:12,802
Please... Please, just don't...

120
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:19,100
DALEK: Alert. Alert.

121
00:09:19,184 --> 00:09:21,478
The Doctor is detected.

122
00:09:22,228 --> 00:09:24,689
The Doctor is surrounded.

123
00:09:24,773 --> 00:09:28,485
Inform High Command,
we have the Doctor.

124
00:09:28,651 --> 00:09:31,654
Seek. Locate. Destroy.

125
00:09:31,738 --> 00:09:34,949
The Doctor is detected.

126
00:09:37,786 --> 00:09:40,663
Seek. Locate. Destroy.

127
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:42,248
Seek.

128
00:09:50,673 --> 00:09:56,471
DALEK: (GARBLED) The Doctor is escaping.

129
00:09:57,180 --> 00:10:01,935
What are these words?

130
00:10:02,018 --> 00:10:05,730
Explain. Explain.

131
00:10:18,201 --> 00:10:20,161
ANDROGAR: The High Council
is in emergency session.

132
00:10:20,411 --> 00:10:22,956
-They have plans of their own.
-GENERAL: To hell with the High Council.

133
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:26,918
Their plans have already failed.
Gallifrey's still in the line of fire.

134
00:10:27,043 --> 00:10:29,712
So, he was there, then.

135
00:10:32,006 --> 00:10:35,718
He left a message.
A written warning for the Daleks.

136
00:10:35,844 --> 00:10:39,430
-He's a fool.
-No, he's a madman.

137
00:10:39,556 --> 00:10:42,642
As you can see, sir, all
Dalek fleets surrounding the planet

138
00:10:42,725 --> 00:10:46,563
are now converging on the capitol,
but the Sky Trenches are holding.

139
00:10:46,688 --> 00:10:48,731
(CRASH)

140
00:10:50,942 --> 00:10:53,111
Where did he go next?

141
00:10:53,236 --> 00:10:56,156
What does it matter?
This is their biggest ever attack.

142
00:10:56,239 --> 00:10:58,950
-Sir, they're throwing everything at us.
-Sir?

143
00:10:59,075 --> 00:11:01,703
We have a security breach
to the Time Vaults.

144
00:11:06,749 --> 00:11:08,668
The Omega Arsenal.

145
00:11:08,751 --> 00:11:11,254
Where all the forbidden weapons
are locked away.

146
00:11:11,379 --> 00:11:14,549
They're not forbidden any more.
We've used them all against the Daleks.

147
00:11:15,550 --> 00:11:18,428
No. No, we haven't.

148
00:11:23,850 --> 00:11:25,143
The Moment is gone.

149
00:11:25,226 --> 00:11:28,563
I don't understand. What is the Moment?
I've never heard of it.

150
00:11:30,231 --> 00:11:32,650
The galaxy eater.

151
00:11:32,775 --> 00:11:34,944
The final work
of the ancients of Gallifrey.

152
00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:39,991
A weapon so powerful,
the operating system became sentient.

153
00:11:40,742 --> 00:11:44,787
According to legend,
it developed a conscience.

154
00:11:44,913 --> 00:11:46,581
And we've never used it?

155
00:11:46,664 --> 00:11:49,709
How do you use a weapon
of ultimate mass destruction

156
00:11:49,792 --> 00:11:51,628
when it can stand in judgement on you?

157
00:11:54,214 --> 00:11:57,300
GENERAL: There is only one man
who would even try.

158
00:12:05,725 --> 00:12:07,727
OLD DOCTOR: Time Lords of Gallifrey,

159
00:12:08,645 --> 00:12:10,939
Daleks of Skaro,

160
00:12:11,022 --> 00:12:14,108
I serve notice on you all.

161
00:12:14,192 --> 00:12:18,196
Too long have I stayed my hand.
No more.

162
00:12:19,530 --> 00:12:23,243
Today, you leave me no choice.

163
00:12:23,326 --> 00:12:26,663
Today, this war will end.

164
00:12:27,664 --> 00:12:29,666
No more.

165
00:12:30,708 --> 00:12:32,669
No more.

166
00:13:20,675 --> 00:13:22,593
Now,

167
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:26,556
how do you work?

168
00:13:27,598 --> 00:13:30,685
Why is there never a big red button?

169
00:13:41,821 --> 00:13:43,948
Hello?

170
00:13:45,241 --> 00:13:47,910
-Is somebody there?
-FEMALE VOICE: It's nothing.

171
00:13:47,994 --> 00:13:49,871
It's just a wolf.

172
00:13:49,954 --> 00:13:51,289
-Don't sit on that!
-Why not?

173
00:13:51,372 --> 00:13:53,207
Because it's not a chair,

174
00:13:53,291 --> 00:13:55,293
it's the most dangerous weapon
in the universe.

175
00:14:00,131 --> 00:14:02,675
Why can't it be both?

176
00:14:04,594 --> 00:14:07,013
Why'd you park so far away?

177
00:14:08,056 --> 00:14:10,183
Didn't you want her to see it?

178
00:14:10,266 --> 00:14:13,770
-Want who to see?
-(WHISPERS) The Tardis.

179
00:14:14,729 --> 00:14:16,606
You walked for miles.

180
00:14:16,689 --> 00:14:19,901
-And miles and miles and miles.
-I was thinking!

181
00:14:19,984 --> 00:14:23,446
-I heard you.
-You heard me?

182
00:14:24,155 --> 00:14:26,616
"No more."

183
00:14:28,493 --> 00:14:29,744
No more.

184
00:14:29,827 --> 00:14:32,413
-No more.
-No more.

185
00:14:32,497 --> 00:14:34,040
-No...
-No more.

186
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:35,333
-Stop it.
-No more!

187
00:14:35,416 --> 00:14:38,294
-No more.
-Who are you?

188
00:14:39,754 --> 00:14:41,297
(WHIRR)

189
00:14:41,381 --> 00:14:44,175
It's activated. Get out of here.

190
00:14:44,258 --> 00:14:45,301
-(SIZZLING)
-Ow!

191
00:14:45,385 --> 00:14:47,929
-What's wrong?
-The interface is hot.

192
00:14:48,012 --> 00:14:50,390
Well, I do my best.

193
00:14:51,891 --> 00:14:53,893
There's a power source inside...

194
00:15:00,149 --> 00:15:01,692
You're the interface?

195
00:15:01,776 --> 00:15:04,695
They must have told you
the Moment had a conscience.

196
00:15:06,739 --> 00:15:07,907
Hello!

197
00:15:09,075 --> 00:15:11,285
Aw, look at you.

198
00:15:11,369 --> 00:15:13,413
Stuck between a girl and a box.

199
00:15:13,496 --> 00:15:17,083
-Story of your life, eh, Doctor?
-You know me?

200
00:15:19,001 --> 00:15:21,087
I hear you.

201
00:15:21,170 --> 00:15:22,755
All of you,

202
00:15:22,839 --> 00:15:26,092
jangling around
in that dusty old head of yours.

203
00:15:26,175 --> 00:15:28,344
I chose this face and form
especially for you.

204
00:15:29,178 --> 00:15:31,347
It's from your past.

205
00:15:31,681 --> 00:15:34,016
Or possibly your future.
I always get those two mixed up.

206
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:36,727
-I don't have a future.
-I think I'm called, erm...

207
00:15:38,104 --> 00:15:40,231
Rose Tyler.

208
00:15:40,314 --> 00:15:43,776
No. Yes. No, sorry.
In this form,

209
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:46,237
I'm called

210
00:15:48,406 --> 00:15:50,491
Bad Wolf.

211
00:15:52,076 --> 00:15:54,996
Are you afraid
of the big bad wolf, Doctor?

212
00:15:55,079 --> 00:15:56,956
Stop calling me "Doctor"”.

213
00:15:57,039 --> 00:15:59,417
-That's the name in your head.
-It shouldn't be.

214
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:02,879
I've been fighting this war
for a long time.

215
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:05,131
I've lost the right to be the Doctor.

216
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:08,426
Then you're the one to save us all.

217
00:16:09,427 --> 00:16:11,012
Yes.

218
00:16:11,095 --> 00:16:13,306
If I ever develop an ego,
you've got the job.

219
00:16:21,564 --> 00:16:24,775
If you have been inside my head,

220
00:16:25,234 --> 00:16:27,612
then you know what I have seen.

221
00:16:28,779 --> 00:16:30,907
The suffering.

222
00:16:31,449 --> 00:16:34,619
Every moment in time and space
is burning.

223
00:16:35,578 --> 00:16:37,830
It must end.

224
00:16:37,914 --> 00:16:41,417
And I intend to end it
the only way I can.

225
00:16:42,084 --> 00:16:44,754
And you're going to use me to end it

226
00:16:44,879 --> 00:16:48,633
by killing them all,
Daleks and Time Lords alike.

227
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:51,552
I could.

228
00:16:51,636 --> 00:16:54,430
But there will be consequences for you.

229
00:16:54,514 --> 00:16:58,100
I have no desire to survive this.

230
00:17:06,943 --> 00:17:09,195
Then that's your punishment.

231
00:17:09,695 --> 00:17:14,742
If you do this, if you kill them all,
then that's the consequence.

232
00:17:18,871 --> 00:17:21,624
You live.

233
00:17:23,084 --> 00:17:24,502
Gallifrey...

234
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:27,922
You're going to burn it,

235
00:17:29,298 --> 00:17:33,177
and all those Daleks with it,
but all those children, too.

236
00:17:35,972 --> 00:17:38,933
How many children
on Gallifrey right now?

237
00:17:40,309 --> 00:17:42,687
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

238
00:17:42,770 --> 00:17:44,855
DOCTOR: I don't know.

239
00:17:47,858 --> 00:17:50,820
One day, you will count them.

240
00:17:52,154 --> 00:17:54,323
One terrible night.

241
00:17:58,369 --> 00:18:00,746
Do you want to see
what that will turn you into?

242
00:18:03,332 --> 00:18:05,501
Come on, aren't you curious?

243
00:18:05,585 --> 00:18:07,837
(WHOOSH)

244
00:18:08,838 --> 00:18:11,674
I'm opening windows on your future.

245
00:18:14,594 --> 00:18:17,054
The tangle in time
through the days to come

246
00:18:17,179 --> 00:18:19,682
to the man today will make of you.

247
00:18:25,563 --> 00:18:27,148
Okay. I wasn't expecting that.

248
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:34,363
But the Time War's over. Why have you
brought us here to look at a painting?

249
00:18:34,447 --> 00:18:37,867
KATE: The painting only serves
as Elizabeth's credentials,

250
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:41,287
proof that the letter is from her.
It's not why you're here.

251
00:18:46,751 --> 00:18:48,586
ELIZABETH: My dearest love,

252
00:18:48,669 --> 00:18:52,214
I hope the painting known as
Gallifrey Falls will serve as proof

253
00:18:52,298 --> 00:18:55,092
that it is your Elizabeth
who writes to you now.

254
00:18:55,176 --> 00:18:57,428
You will recall
that you pledged yourself

255
00:18:57,511 --> 00:18:59,305
to the safety of my kingdom.

256
00:18:59,388 --> 00:19:03,142
In this capacity, I have appointed you
as curator of the Under-Gallery,

257
00:19:03,225 --> 00:19:05,561
where deadly danger to England
is locked away.

258
00:19:06,228 --> 00:19:08,564
Should any disturbance occur
within its walls,

259
00:19:08,814 --> 00:19:12,902
it is my wish that you be summoned.
Godspeed, gentle husband.

260
00:19:17,281 --> 00:19:19,784
-What happened?
-Easier to show you.

261
00:19:27,625 --> 00:19:29,710
(PHONE RINGS)

262
00:19:31,379 --> 00:19:32,755
McGillop.

263
00:19:39,929 --> 00:19:42,682
But that's not possible.
I was just...

264
00:19:43,974 --> 00:19:47,895
Understood, sir,
but why would I take it there?

265
00:19:59,281 --> 00:20:02,660
CLARA: Elizabeth I?
You knew her, then?

266
00:20:04,995 --> 00:20:06,997
A long time ago.

267
00:20:19,009 --> 00:20:21,345
(HOOFBEATS APPROACHING)

268
00:20:21,429 --> 00:20:23,431
DOCTOR: Allons-y!

269
00:20:27,643 --> 00:20:29,645
There you go, Your Majesty,
what did I tell you?

270
00:20:30,521 --> 00:20:31,814
Bigger on the inside.

271
00:20:31,897 --> 00:20:34,108
The door isn't.
You nearly took my head off.

272
00:20:34,191 --> 00:20:36,652
It's normally me who does that.
(GIGGLES)

273
00:20:37,570 --> 00:20:40,906
ELIZABETH: Tell me, Doctor,
why I'm wasting my time on you.

274
00:20:40,990 --> 00:20:42,908
I have wars to plan.

275
00:20:42,992 --> 00:20:45,077
You have a picnic to eat.

276
00:20:45,161 --> 00:20:47,747
You could help me.

277
00:20:47,830 --> 00:20:50,666
Well, I'm helping you eat the picnic.

278
00:20:53,836 --> 00:20:56,255
But you have a stomach for war.

279
00:20:57,339 --> 00:21:01,093
This face has seen conflict.
It's clear as day.

280
00:21:01,177 --> 00:21:04,138
Oh, I've seen conflict
like you wouldn't believe.

281
00:21:05,097 --> 00:21:07,183
But it wasn't this face.

282
00:21:08,642 --> 00:21:11,604
But never mind that, Your Majesty!
Up on your feet. Hup!

283
00:21:11,687 --> 00:21:13,689
How dare you?
I'm the Queen of England.

284
00:21:13,773 --> 00:21:15,691
I'm not English.

285
00:21:15,858 --> 00:21:17,443
Elizabeth,

286
00:21:17,526 --> 00:21:19,153
will you marry me?

287
00:21:19,236 --> 00:21:21,989
Oh, my dear sweet love,
of course I will.

288
00:21:22,072 --> 00:21:23,741
-Ah! Gotcha!
-My love?

289
00:21:23,991 --> 00:21:27,620
One, the real Elizabeth would never
have accepted my marriage proposal.

290
00:21:27,703 --> 00:21:29,955
Two, the real Elizabeth would notice

291
00:21:30,039 --> 00:21:32,208
when I just casually mention
having a different face.

292
00:21:32,374 --> 00:21:34,794
But then, the real Elizabeth

293
00:21:34,877 --> 00:21:36,921
isn't a shape-shifting alien
from outer space.

294
00:21:37,171 --> 00:21:38,672
And...

295
00:21:39,715 --> 00:21:41,133
-(DING)
-...ding.

296
00:21:41,217 --> 00:21:44,887
-What's that?
-It's a machine that goes "ding".

297
00:21:45,012 --> 00:21:47,723
Made it myself. Lights up
in the presence of shapeshifter DNA.

298
00:21:47,807 --> 00:21:49,141
-(MACHINE DINGS)
-Ooh.

299
00:21:49,225 --> 00:21:51,310
Also, it can microwave frozen dinners
from up to 20 feet,

300
00:21:51,393 --> 00:21:53,562
and download comics from the future.
I never know when to stop.

301
00:21:53,687 --> 00:21:57,358
-My love, I do not understand.
-I'm not your love, and yes, you do.

302
00:21:59,568 --> 00:22:02,112
-You're a Zygon.
-A Zygon?

303
00:22:02,321 --> 00:22:05,366
Oh, stop it, it's over. A Zygon, yes.

304
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:08,744
Big red rubbery thing, covered
in suckers. Surprisingly good kisser.

305
00:22:08,828 --> 00:22:11,372
Do you think the real queen of England
would just decide to share her throne

306
00:22:11,539 --> 00:22:13,499
with any old handsome bloke
in a tight suit,

307
00:22:13,582 --> 00:22:16,669
just 'cause he's got amazing hair
and a nice horse...

308
00:22:16,752 --> 00:22:18,879
(GURGLING ROAR)

309
00:22:19,255 --> 00:22:22,758
Oh, it was the horse!

310
00:22:23,467 --> 00:22:25,094
I'm going to be king.

311
00:22:25,261 --> 00:22:26,846
" -Run!
-What' s happening?

312
00:22:26,929 --> 00:22:29,181
We're being attacked by a
shape-shifting alien from outer space,

313
00:22:29,265 --> 00:22:31,684
-formerly disguised as my horse.
-What does that mean?

314
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:33,602
It means we're going to need
a new horse.

315
00:22:37,106 --> 00:22:38,691
-Where's it going?
-I'll hold it off.

316
00:22:38,774 --> 00:22:40,526
You run. Your people need you.

317
00:22:40,609 --> 00:22:42,903
And I need you alive
for our wedding day.

318
00:22:49,785 --> 00:22:52,454
Oh, good work, Doctor. Nice one.

319
00:22:52,538 --> 00:22:54,373
The Virgin Queen.
So much for history.

320
00:22:59,044 --> 00:23:01,881
Come on! I know you're there!

321
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:06,510
(PANTING)

322
00:23:10,472 --> 00:23:11,640
(ELIZABETH SHRIEKS)

323
00:23:13,225 --> 00:23:16,145
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

324
00:23:16,729 --> 00:23:19,148
Oh, very clever.

325
00:23:20,441 --> 00:23:24,236
Whatever you've got planned,
forget it. I'm the Doctor.

326
00:23:24,320 --> 00:23:26,572
I'm 904 years old.

327
00:23:26,655 --> 00:23:29,658
I'm from the planet Gallifrey
in the constellation of Kasterborous.

328
00:23:29,742 --> 00:23:33,078
I am the oncoming storm,
the bringer of darkness, and you...

329
00:23:33,162 --> 00:23:35,539
are basically just a rabbit,
aren't you?

330
00:23:35,623 --> 00:23:39,919
(FLUSTERED) Okay. Carry on.
Just a general warning.

331
00:23:40,169 --> 00:23:42,254
(DING)

332
00:23:42,338 --> 00:23:44,965
ELIZABETH: Doctor!

333
00:23:49,511 --> 00:23:51,430
Elizabeth!

334
00:23:51,513 --> 00:23:56,268
That thing, explain what it is.
What does it want of us?

335
00:23:56,352 --> 00:23:59,772
That's what I'm trying to find out.
Probably just your planet.

336
00:23:59,855 --> 00:24:01,440
ELIZABETH'S VOICE: Doctor?

337
00:24:01,523 --> 00:24:05,819
Step away from her, Doctor.
That's not me. That's the creature.

338
00:24:05,903 --> 00:24:08,364
How is that possible? She's me!

339
00:24:08,697 --> 00:24:12,034
-Doctor, she's me!
-I am indeed "me".

340
00:24:12,117 --> 00:24:14,870
A compliment that cannot be extended
to yourself.

341
00:24:14,995 --> 00:24:19,124
Extraordinary. The creature
has captured my exact likeness.

342
00:24:19,208 --> 00:24:22,294
-This is exceptional.
-Exceptional?

343
00:24:22,378 --> 00:24:25,381
-A queen would call it impertinent.
-A queen would feel compelled

344
00:24:25,506 --> 00:24:27,633
to admire the skill of the execution,

345
00:24:27,716 --> 00:24:30,636
-before arranging one.
-Argh, it's not working!

346
00:24:30,719 --> 00:24:33,472
One might surmise that the creature
would learn quickly to protect itself

347
00:24:33,555 --> 00:24:35,516
-from any simple means of detection.
-(DING)

348
00:24:35,641 --> 00:24:37,977
Clearly, you understand the creature
better than I.

349
00:24:38,060 --> 00:24:40,396
-But then, you have the advantage.
-(WHOOSHING)

350
00:24:40,521 --> 00:24:44,066
Back! Both of you, now!
That's a time fissure.

351
00:24:44,191 --> 00:24:47,319
A tear in the fabric of reality.
Anything could happen.

352
00:24:50,572 --> 00:24:53,617
For instance, a fez.

353
00:24:58,831 --> 00:25:00,624
This way.

354
00:25:02,251 --> 00:25:04,503
Welcome to the Under-Gallery.

355
00:25:07,047 --> 00:25:09,842
This is where Elizabeth I kept all art

356
00:25:09,925 --> 00:25:12,052
deemed too dangerous
for public consumption.

357
00:25:24,523 --> 00:25:27,443
-Stone dust.
-Is it important?

358
00:25:27,568 --> 00:25:30,112
In 1,200 years, I've never stepped
in anything that wasn't.

359
00:25:31,113 --> 00:25:32,614
(OSGOOD WHEEZES)

360
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:34,700
Oi! You!

361
00:25:34,783 --> 00:25:39,788
-Are you sciencey?
-Oh, um, well, yes.

362
00:25:39,872 --> 00:25:41,874
-Got a name?
-Yes...

363
00:25:41,957 --> 00:25:44,126
Good. I've always wanted to meet
someone called "Yes".

364
00:25:44,209 --> 00:25:46,295
Now, I want this stone dust analysed.

365
00:25:46,420 --> 00:25:49,214
And I want a report, in triplicate,

366
00:25:49,298 --> 00:25:52,217
with lots of graphs and diagrams
and complicated sums,

367
00:25:52,301 --> 00:25:58,057
on my desk, tomorrow morning,
ASAP, pronto, LOL.

368
00:25:58,140 --> 00:26:00,392
See? Job. Do I have a desk?

369
00:26:00,476 --> 00:26:02,227
-No.
-And I want a desk.

370
00:26:02,311 --> 00:26:05,439
Get a team. Analyse the stone dust.

371
00:26:08,150 --> 00:26:10,152
-(WHEEZES)
-Inhaler.

372
00:26:27,753 --> 00:26:29,838
Someday, you could just walk past a fez.

373
00:26:29,922 --> 00:26:31,006
Never gonna happen.

374
00:26:32,716 --> 00:26:34,885
As you instructed.
Nothing has been touched.

375
00:26:40,766 --> 00:26:43,936
This is why we called you in.

376
00:26:44,019 --> 00:26:46,355
CLARA: 3D again.

377
00:26:46,522 --> 00:26:48,524
-Interesting.
-The broken glass?

378
00:26:48,649 --> 00:26:51,944
No, where it's broken from.

379
00:26:55,447 --> 00:26:58,117
Look at the shatter pattern.
The glass in all these paintings

380
00:26:58,200 --> 00:27:00,035
has been broken from the inside.

381
00:27:02,830 --> 00:27:05,124
As you can see,
all the paintings are landscapes.

382
00:27:05,207 --> 00:27:07,793
-No figures of any kind.
-So?

383
00:27:07,876 --> 00:27:09,878
There used to be.

384
00:27:16,135 --> 00:27:19,638
-Something's got out of the paintings?
-Lots of somethings.

385
00:27:19,721 --> 00:27:21,515
Dangerous.

386
00:27:21,598 --> 00:27:24,601
This whole place has been searched.
There's nothing here that shouldn't be,

387
00:27:24,893 --> 00:27:26,562
and nothing's got out.

388
00:27:28,856 --> 00:27:31,150
-Oh, no, not now.
-Doctor, what is it?

389
00:27:31,233 --> 00:27:33,318
No, not now! I'm busy.

390
00:27:33,402 --> 00:27:36,155
-Is it to do with the paintings?
-No, no. This is different.

391
00:27:36,238 --> 00:27:39,283
I remember this. Almost remember.

392
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:47,166
Oh, of course.

393
00:27:48,584 --> 00:27:50,919
This is where I come in.

394
00:27:54,590 --> 00:27:56,091
Geronimo!

395
00:27:56,175 --> 00:27:57,759
-Doctor!
-Wait!

396
00:28:09,104 --> 00:28:11,648
-Who is this man?
-That's just what I was wondering.

397
00:28:11,773 --> 00:28:15,986
Oh, that is skinny.
That is proper skinny.

398
00:28:16,111 --> 00:28:18,822
I've never seen it from the outside.
It's like a special effect.

399
00:28:19,448 --> 00:28:21,867
Oi, matchstick man.

400
00:28:24,286 --> 00:28:25,370
You're not...

401
00:28:41,053 --> 00:28:42,971
-Compensating?
-For what?

402
00:28:43,055 --> 00:28:46,016
-Regeneration. It's a lottery.
-(SARCASTIC) Oh, he's cool.

403
00:28:46,141 --> 00:28:48,477
Isn't he cool?
"I'm the Doctor, and I'm all cool.

404
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:50,687
"Oops, I'm wearing sand shoes.”

405
00:28:50,812 --> 00:28:53,523
-What are you doing here? I'm busy.
-Oh, busy? I see.

406
00:28:53,649 --> 00:28:55,692
Is that what we're calling it, eh? Eh?

407
00:28:55,817 --> 00:28:58,820
-Hello, ladies.
-Don't start.

408
00:28:58,904 --> 00:29:01,114
Listen, what you get up to in
the privacy of your own regeneration

409
00:29:01,198 --> 00:29:02,866
-is your business...
-One of them is a Zygon.

410
00:29:02,991 --> 00:29:05,494
Ugh. I'm not judging you.

411
00:29:05,577 --> 00:29:07,162
(WHOOSH)

412
00:29:12,251 --> 00:29:13,919
-Oh!
-Oh, lovely!

413
00:29:15,045 --> 00:29:17,214
Your Majesties?
Probably a good time to run.

414
00:29:17,339 --> 00:29:19,007
BOTH: But what about the creature?

415
00:29:19,091 --> 00:29:21,218
Elizabeth, whichever one of you
is the real one, turn and run

416
00:29:21,343 --> 00:29:22,844
in the opposite direction
to the other one.

417
00:29:22,928 --> 00:29:25,180
-BOTH: Of course, my love.
-Stay alive, my love.

418
00:29:25,264 --> 00:29:27,391
-I am not done with you yet.
-(MUFFLED) Oh!

419
00:29:30,018 --> 00:29:32,062
-Thanks. Lovely.
-I understand.

420
00:29:32,187 --> 00:29:35,107
Live for me, my darling.
We shall be together again.

421
00:29:39,695 --> 00:29:41,405
Well, won't that be nice.

422
00:29:42,614 --> 00:29:44,533
-One of those was a Zygon?
-Yeah.

423
00:29:44,616 --> 00:29:46,910
Big red rubbery thing covered
in suckers? Venom sacs in the tongue?

424
00:29:47,035 --> 00:29:48,870
-Yeah, I'm getting the point, thank you.
-Nice.

425
00:29:48,954 --> 00:29:52,207
-CLARA: Doctor, is that you?
-Ah, hello, Clara! Can you hear me?

426
00:29:52,291 --> 00:29:54,876
Yeah, it's me. We can hear you.
Where are you?

427
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:57,921
-Where are we?
-England, 1562.

428
00:29:58,046 --> 00:30:00,424
-Who are you talking to?
-BOTH: Myself.

429
00:30:00,549 --> 00:30:02,426
Can you come back through?

430
00:30:02,551 --> 00:30:06,596
Physical passage may not be possible
in both directions. It's... Ah!

431
00:30:06,722 --> 00:30:09,766
Hang on. (SHOUTS) Fez incoming!

432
00:30:15,105 --> 00:30:16,440
Nothing here.

433
00:30:17,399 --> 00:30:19,568
So where did it go?

434
00:30:29,411 --> 00:30:32,748
CLARA: Who's he talking to?
KATE: He said, himself.

435
00:30:34,124 --> 00:30:35,459
Keep him talking.

436
00:30:35,584 --> 00:30:36,877
KATE: Malcolm?

437
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:39,963
Malcolm, I need you to send me
one of my father's incident files.

438
00:30:40,088 --> 00:30:44,760
Codenamed "Cromer". '70s or '80s,
depending on the dating protocol.

439
00:30:44,926 --> 00:30:46,845
(SNARLING)

440
00:30:47,471 --> 00:30:50,140
Okay. You used to be me.
You've done all this before.

441
00:30:50,265 --> 00:30:52,351
-What happens next?
-I don't remember.

442
00:30:53,643 --> 00:30:57,147
-How can you forget this?
-Hey, hang on, it's not my fault.

443
00:30:57,272 --> 00:31:00,692
You're obviously not paying
enough attention. Reverse the polarity.

444
00:31:03,028 --> 00:31:05,155
(SCREWDRIVERS BUZZING)

445
00:31:06,323 --> 00:31:08,075
It's not working.

446
00:31:08,158 --> 00:31:10,410
-We're both reversing the polarity.
-Yes, I know that.

447
00:31:10,494 --> 00:31:12,496
There's two of us. I'm reversing it,
and you're reversing it back again.

448
00:31:12,621 --> 00:31:15,791
-We're confusing the polarity.
-(WHOOSH)

449
00:31:17,167 --> 00:31:20,128
Anyone lose a fez?

450
00:31:20,295 --> 00:31:23,465
You.
How can you be here?

451
00:31:23,882 --> 00:31:26,468
More to the point, why are you here?

452
00:31:26,551 --> 00:31:31,473
Good afternoon.
I'm looking for the Doctor.

453
00:31:32,808 --> 00:31:35,644
Well, you've certainly come
to the right place.

454
00:31:35,852 --> 00:31:39,314
Good. Right. Who are you boys?

455
00:31:40,565 --> 00:31:43,151
Of course. Are you his companions?

456
00:31:43,235 --> 00:31:46,822
-His companions?
-They get younger all the time.

457
00:31:46,905 --> 00:31:50,492
Well, if you could point me in
the general direction of the Doctor...

458
00:31:59,668 --> 00:32:01,837
-Really?
-Yeah.

459
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:04,214
-Really.
-You're me?

460
00:32:04,339 --> 00:32:06,716
-Both of you?
-Yup.

461
00:32:06,842 --> 00:32:09,511
-Even that one?
-Yes!

462
00:32:09,594 --> 00:32:12,639
You're my future selves?

463
00:32:12,722 --> 00:32:16,560
-BOTH: Yes.
-Am I having a mid-Llife crisis?

464
00:32:17,561 --> 00:32:19,813
Why are you pointing
your screwdrivers like that?

465
00:32:19,896 --> 00:32:22,691
They are scientific instruments,
not water-pistols!

466
00:32:23,859 --> 00:32:25,527
You look like you've seen a ghost.

467
00:32:26,862 --> 00:32:30,073
Still, loving the posh, gravelly thing.
It's very convincing.

468
00:32:30,198 --> 00:32:32,117
Brave words, Dick Van Dyke.

469
00:32:32,534 --> 00:32:34,453
MAN: Encircle them!

470
00:32:34,786 --> 00:32:36,872
Which of you is the Doctor?

471
00:32:38,540 --> 00:32:41,126
The Queen of England is bewitched.
I would have the Doctor's head.

472
00:32:41,251 --> 00:32:45,630
Well, this has all the makings
of your lucky day.

473
00:32:47,299 --> 00:32:49,009
(WHISPERS) I think there's
three of them now.

474
00:32:49,092 --> 00:32:51,052
KATE: There's a precedent for that.

475
00:32:51,720 --> 00:32:55,765
-What is that?
-Oh, the pointing again.

476
00:32:55,891 --> 00:32:57,350
They're screwdrivers.

477
00:32:57,434 --> 00:32:59,853
What are you going to do,
assemble a cabinet at them?

478
00:32:59,936 --> 00:33:02,564
That thing, what witchcraft is it?

479
00:33:02,647 --> 00:33:07,194
Ah! Yes, now that you mention it,
that is witchcraft.

480
00:33:07,277 --> 00:33:10,113
Yes, yes, yes, witchy witchcraft.
Hello?

481
00:33:10,238 --> 00:33:12,616
Hello in there, excuse me, hello.

482
00:33:12,908 --> 00:33:15,660
Am I talking to
the wicked witch of the well?

483
00:33:15,785 --> 00:33:19,247
-He means you.
-Why am I the witch?

484
00:33:19,498 --> 00:33:21,708
-Clara?
-Hello?

485
00:33:21,791 --> 00:33:23,793
Clara, hi. Hello.

486
00:33:23,919 --> 00:33:26,129
Hello. Would you mind telling
these prattling mortals

487
00:33:26,254 --> 00:33:29,799
-to get themselves begone?
-What he said.

488
00:33:29,925 --> 00:33:33,470
-(WHISPERS) A tiny bit more colour?
-Right.

489
00:33:33,595 --> 00:33:36,598
(HESITANT) Prattling mortals!
Off you... pop!

490
00:33:36,681 --> 00:33:39,643
-Or I'll turn you all into frogs.
-Oh.

491
00:33:39,768 --> 00:33:43,647
-Frogs. Nice. You heard her.
-Doctor, what's going on?

492
00:33:43,772 --> 00:33:47,317
It's, er, a timey-wimey thing.

493
00:33:47,442 --> 00:33:50,278
Timey what? "Timey-wimey"?

494
00:33:50,362 --> 00:33:52,739
I've no idea
where he picks that stuff up.

495
00:33:52,822 --> 00:33:55,283
-The Queen!
-SOLDIERS: The Queen!

496
00:33:55,367 --> 00:33:59,454
You don't seem to be kneeling.
How tremendously brave of you.

497
00:33:59,538 --> 00:34:01,331
Which one are you?
What happened to the other one?

498
00:34:01,456 --> 00:34:03,291
Indisposed.

499
00:34:03,375 --> 00:34:06,253
-Long live the Queen.
-SOLDIERS: Long live the Queen!

500
00:34:06,336 --> 00:34:08,672
Arrest these men.
Take them to the Tower.

501
00:34:08,797 --> 00:34:11,675
That is not the Queen of England.
That's an alien duplicate.

502
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:13,677
And you can take it from him,
'cause he's really checked.

503
00:34:13,802 --> 00:34:15,512
-Oh, shut up.
-Venom sacs in the tongue.

504
00:34:15,637 --> 00:34:17,681
-Seriously, stop it.
-No, hang on. The Tower.

505
00:34:17,806 --> 00:34:20,350
Did you say the Tower?
Ah, yes. Brilliant.

506
00:34:20,475 --> 00:34:23,186
Love the Tower. Breakfast
at 8:00, please. Will there be wi-fi?

507
00:34:23,311 --> 00:34:26,356
Are you capable of speaking
without flapping your hands about?

508
00:34:26,481 --> 00:34:28,984
Yes. No. I demand to be incarcerated

509
00:34:29,067 --> 00:34:31,194
in the Tower immediately
with my co-conspirators,

510
00:34:31,319 --> 00:34:33,446
-Sandshoes and Grandad.
-"Grandad"?

511
00:34:33,530 --> 00:34:35,615
-They're not sand shoes.
-Yes, they are.

512
00:34:35,699 --> 00:34:38,326
Silence. The Tower is not
to be taken lightly.

513
00:34:38,410 --> 00:34:41,121
-ELIZABETH: Very few emerge again.
-KATE: Dear God, that man's clever.

514
00:34:41,204 --> 00:34:43,206
-Come on.
-Where are we going?

515
00:34:43,331 --> 00:34:45,875
My office, otherwise known as
the Tower of London.

516
00:34:49,504 --> 00:34:51,840
JAILER: Oi, you lot, get in there.

517
00:34:55,385 --> 00:34:57,178
(DOOR SLAMS)

518
00:35:01,391 --> 00:35:03,393
TENTH DOCTOR:
Three of us in one cell?

519
00:35:03,518 --> 00:35:06,187
That's going to cause some nasty
anomalies if we don't get out soon.

520
00:35:06,271 --> 00:35:07,689
What are you doing?

521
00:35:09,024 --> 00:35:11,401
-Getting us out.
-The sonic won't work on that.

522
00:35:11,526 --> 00:35:13,737
It's too primitive.

523
00:35:13,862 --> 00:35:16,364
Shall we ask for a better quality
of door, so we can escape?

524
00:35:16,448 --> 00:35:20,243
Okay, so the Queen of England
is now a Zygon.

525
00:35:20,368 --> 00:35:22,912
Never mind that.
Why are we all together?

526
00:35:23,038 --> 00:35:25,123
Why are we all here?

527
00:35:26,875 --> 00:35:31,254
Me and Chinny, we were surprised,
but you came looking for us.

528
00:35:31,379 --> 00:35:33,048
You knew it was going to happen.
Who told you?

529
00:35:34,049 --> 00:35:35,967
Oi! "Chinny"?

530
00:35:36,051 --> 00:35:37,636
Yeah, you do have a chin.

531
00:35:39,971 --> 00:35:43,058
OSGOOD: Marble, granite...

532
00:35:43,141 --> 00:35:45,435
A lot of different stone,

533
00:35:45,560 --> 00:35:48,229
but none of it from
the fabric of the building.

534
00:35:48,313 --> 00:35:51,107
It's like somebody smashed up
a lot of old statues.

535
00:35:51,232 --> 00:35:55,028
-Are there any missing?
-Don't think so.

536
00:35:55,111 --> 00:35:57,072
Why would anyone do that, anyway?

537
00:35:58,406 --> 00:36:01,368
I mean, I know we're meant
to keep an open mind,

538
00:36:01,451 --> 00:36:05,246
but are we supposed to believe in
creatures that can hide in oil paintings

539
00:36:05,330 --> 00:36:08,249
and have some sort of a grudge
against statues?

540
00:36:08,333 --> 00:36:10,752
-(INHALES)
-You all right?

541
00:36:12,128 --> 00:36:14,089
We have to go, right now.
This minute.

542
00:36:14,172 --> 00:36:17,258
-What's wrong?
-The things from the paintings.

543
00:36:17,801 --> 00:36:19,761
I know why they smashed the statues.

544
00:36:21,262 --> 00:36:23,807
-Why?
-Because they needed somewhere to hide.

545
00:36:27,977 --> 00:36:30,188
(SNARLING)

546
00:36:34,943 --> 00:36:37,362
-(MUFFLED SCREAMING)
- (SHRIEKS)

547
00:36:42,450 --> 00:36:44,494
(SCREAMS)

548
00:36:57,841 --> 00:36:59,843
(INHALES)

549
00:36:59,968 --> 00:37:02,345
The Doctor will save me.
The Doctor will save me.

550
00:37:02,470 --> 00:37:05,140
The Doctor will save me,
the Doctor will save me...

551
00:37:06,307 --> 00:37:08,309
(RUSTLING)

552
00:37:08,393 --> 00:37:11,896
Excuse me. I'm going to need my inhaler.

553
00:37:12,814 --> 00:37:15,233
I so hate it
when I get one with a defect.

554
00:37:15,984 --> 00:37:19,988
Ooh, you've got some perfectly horrible
memories in here, haven't you?

555
00:37:22,157 --> 00:37:24,159
So jealous of your pretty sister.

556
00:37:24,242 --> 00:37:27,370
I don't blame you.
I wish I'd copied her.

557
00:37:29,164 --> 00:37:31,791
So do 1.

558
00:37:31,875 --> 00:37:34,502
Oh, for goodness' sake.

559
00:37:37,422 --> 00:37:39,966
KATE: The Doctor
will be trying to send us a message.

560
00:37:40,049 --> 00:37:43,845
We're looking for a string of numerals,
from around 1550, approximately.

561
00:37:43,928 --> 00:37:48,516
Priority one. I'm going to need access
to the Black Archive.

562
00:37:51,936 --> 00:37:55,398
Black Archive. Highest security rating
on the planet.

563
00:37:55,523 --> 00:37:58,818
The entire staff have their memories
wiped at the end of every shift.

564
00:37:58,902 --> 00:38:02,071
Automated memory filters
on the ceiling. Access, please.

565
00:38:02,197 --> 00:38:04,032
Ma'am.

566
00:38:08,119 --> 00:38:12,248
-Atkins, isn't it?
-Yes, ma'am. First day here.

567
00:38:12,373 --> 00:38:14,459
Been here ten years.

568
00:38:19,964 --> 00:38:21,591
(DOOR LOCKING)

569
00:38:21,716 --> 00:38:23,885
CLARA: Lock and key?
Bit basic, isn't it?

570
00:38:23,968 --> 00:38:26,596
Can't afford electronic security
down here. Got to keep the Doctor out.

571
00:38:26,721 --> 00:38:29,516
The whole of the Tower
is Tardis-proofed.

572
00:38:29,599 --> 00:38:31,893
He really wouldn't approve
of the collection.

573
00:38:31,976 --> 00:38:34,604
-But you let me in.
-You have a top-level security rating

574
00:38:34,729 --> 00:38:37,690
-from your last visit.
-Sorry, my what?

575
00:38:37,774 --> 00:38:40,860
KATE: Apologies. We have to screen
all his known associates.

576
00:38:40,944 --> 00:38:43,029
Can't have information
about the Doctor and the Tardis

577
00:38:43,112 --> 00:38:45,448
falling into the wrong hands.

578
00:38:45,573 --> 00:38:48,493
The consequences could be disastrous.

579
00:38:51,246 --> 00:38:54,916
-What is that?
-Time travel.

580
00:38:55,500 --> 00:38:58,753
A vortex manipulator
bequeathed to the UNIT archive

581
00:38:58,837 --> 00:39:00,880
by Captain Jack Harkness
on the occasion of his death.

582
00:39:00,964 --> 00:39:02,799
Well, one of them.

583
00:39:02,924 --> 00:39:06,135
No one can know we have this,
not even our allies.

584
00:39:06,261 --> 00:39:08,638
-Why not?
-Think about it.

585
00:39:08,763 --> 00:39:11,307
Americans with the ability
to rewrite history.

586
00:39:11,432 --> 00:39:13,142
You've seen their movies.

587
00:39:17,313 --> 00:39:20,942
Okay, so this is how
we're going to rescue the Doctor?

588
00:39:21,985 --> 00:39:24,779
KATE: Not sure there's enough power
for a two-way trip.

589
00:39:24,863 --> 00:39:27,824
In any event, we don't have
the activation code.

590
00:39:27,949 --> 00:39:31,160
The Doctor knows we have this,
so he's always kept the code from us.

591
00:39:31,286 --> 00:39:33,329
-(PHONE RINGS)
-Let's hope he changes his mind.

592
00:39:33,454 --> 00:39:35,039
Yes?

593
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:41,129
Well, if you've found it, photograph it
and send it to my phone.

594
00:39:46,885 --> 00:39:48,136
Um, Kate?

595
00:39:49,220 --> 00:39:51,347
Should they be here?
Why have they followed us?

596
00:39:51,472 --> 00:39:53,808
Oh, they've probably just finished

597
00:39:53,892 --> 00:39:56,811
-disposing of the humans a bit early.
-The hu...?

598
00:39:57,729 --> 00:39:59,480
Dear me.

599
00:39:59,564 --> 00:40:02,901
I really do get into character, don't I?

600
00:40:21,210 --> 00:40:23,004
OSGOOD 2: The Under-Gallery
is secured.

601
00:40:23,087 --> 00:40:26,299
ZYGON: Prepare to dispose
of one more human.

602
00:40:26,382 --> 00:40:29,010
We have acquired the device.

603
00:40:30,345 --> 00:40:31,512
(MANIPULATOR BEEPS)

604
00:40:31,596 --> 00:40:33,681
-Activation code, right?
-(SNARLS)

605
00:40:38,853 --> 00:40:41,564
In theory, I can trigger
an isolated sonic shift

606
00:40:41,689 --> 00:40:45,360
among the molecules,
and the door should disintegrate.

607
00:40:45,443 --> 00:40:48,029
You'd have to calculate the harmonic
resonance of the entire structure

608
00:40:48,112 --> 00:40:50,990
down to a sub-atomic level.
Even the sonic would take years.

609
00:40:51,074 --> 00:40:54,369
No, no. The sonic would take centuries.

610
00:40:54,452 --> 00:40:58,706
Well, we might as well get started.
Help to pass the "timey-wimey".

611
00:41:00,208 --> 00:41:01,918
Do you have to talk like children?

612
00:41:02,043 --> 00:41:05,046
What is it that makes you so ashamed
of being a grown-up?

613
00:41:07,590 --> 00:41:12,512
Oh, the way you both look at me.
What is that?

614
00:41:12,595 --> 00:41:16,224
I'm trying to think of a better word
than "dread".

615
00:41:17,725 --> 00:41:19,727
Must be really recent, for you.

616
00:41:20,269 --> 00:41:21,896
Recent?

617
00:41:23,231 --> 00:41:26,192
The Time War. The last day.
The day you killed them all.

618
00:41:26,275 --> 00:41:29,070
-The day we killed them all.
-Same thing.

619
00:41:32,573 --> 00:41:35,660
It's history for them. All decided.

620
00:41:36,244 --> 00:41:39,580
They think their future is real.
They don't know it's still up to you.

621
00:41:40,248 --> 00:41:41,791
I don't talk about it.

622
00:41:41,916 --> 00:41:44,043
You're not talking about it.
There's no one else here.

623
00:41:44,127 --> 00:41:48,089
Go on. Ask them.
Ask them what you need to know.

624
00:41:51,759 --> 00:41:54,679
-Did you ever count?
-Count what?

625
00:41:55,847 --> 00:41:58,766
How many children there were
on Gallifrey, that day.

626
00:42:03,479 --> 00:42:05,606
I've absolutely no idea.

627
00:42:05,690 --> 00:42:07,984
How old are you now?

628
00:42:08,943 --> 00:42:12,238
I don't know. I lose track.

629
00:42:12,321 --> 00:42:15,450
Twelve hundred and something,
I think. Unless I'm lying.

630
00:42:15,658 --> 00:42:17,952
I can't remember if I'm lying
about my age, that's how old I am.

631
00:42:18,036 --> 00:42:20,913
Four hundred years older than me.
And in all that time,

632
00:42:20,997 --> 00:42:23,708
you never even wondered
how many there were?

633
00:42:24,625 --> 00:42:27,336
You never once counted?

634
00:42:27,962 --> 00:42:29,672
Tell me,

635
00:42:29,797 --> 00:42:31,966
what would be the point?

636
00:42:32,050 --> 00:42:34,761
2.47 billion.

637
00:42:34,844 --> 00:42:36,179
You did count!

638
00:42:38,973 --> 00:42:42,477
You forgot? Four hundred years?
Is that all it takes?

639
00:42:43,478 --> 00:42:45,354
-I moved on.
-Where?

640
00:42:45,480 --> 00:42:47,857
Where can you be now, that you can
forget something like that?

641
00:42:47,982 --> 00:42:49,817
-Spoilers.
-No.

642
00:42:49,901 --> 00:42:52,487
No, no, no. For once, I would like
to know where I'm going.

643
00:42:52,570 --> 00:42:55,156
No, you really wouldn't.

644
00:42:57,408 --> 00:43:01,454
I don't know who you are,
either of you.

645
00:43:01,537 --> 00:43:04,540
-I haven't got the faintest idea.
-They're you.

646
00:43:06,042 --> 00:43:08,669
They're what you become,
if you destroy Gallifrey.

647
00:43:10,171 --> 00:43:14,008
The man who regrets,
and the man who forgets.

648
00:43:15,384 --> 00:43:17,553
The moment is coming.

649
00:43:18,387 --> 00:43:20,848
The moment is me.
You have to decide.

650
00:43:29,023 --> 00:43:31,442
-No.
_IINOII?

651
00:43:31,692 --> 00:43:33,194
Just...

652
00:43:34,028 --> 00:43:35,196
no.

653
00:43:35,363 --> 00:43:39,033
-(LAUGHS QUIETLY)
-Is something funny?

654
00:43:39,117 --> 00:43:41,994
-Did I miss a funny thing?
-Sorry.

655
00:43:42,078 --> 00:43:45,039
It just occurred to me,
this is what I'm like when I'm alone.

656
00:43:46,624 --> 00:43:48,751
It's the same screwdriver.

657
00:43:53,881 --> 00:43:58,136
Same software, different case.

658
00:44:03,391 --> 00:44:04,433
Ah.

659
00:44:06,727 --> 00:44:10,356
-Four hundred years.
-Sorry?

660
00:44:10,439 --> 00:44:13,943
Well, at a software level, they're all
the same device, aren't they?

661
00:44:14,068 --> 00:44:16,404
Same software, different case.

662
00:44:16,487 --> 00:44:18,573
(HESITANT) Yes, so...

663
00:44:18,739 --> 00:44:19,740
So...

664
00:44:19,907 --> 00:44:23,786
It would take centuries
for the screwdriver to calculate

665
00:44:23,911 --> 00:44:26,122
how to disintegrate the door.

666
00:44:26,247 --> 00:44:29,792
Scanning the door,
implanting the calculation

667
00:44:29,917 --> 00:44:33,462
as a permanent subroutine
in the software architecture...

668
00:44:33,588 --> 00:44:37,300
And if you really are me,

669
00:44:37,425 --> 00:44:39,886
with your sand shoes
and your Dickie-bow,

670
00:44:39,969 --> 00:44:43,306
and that screwdriver is still mine,

671
00:44:44,473 --> 00:44:47,310
that calculation is still going on.

672
00:44:48,603 --> 00:44:50,980
(SCREWDRIVER HUMMING)

673
00:44:51,105 --> 00:44:54,150
-Yeah! Still going.
-(SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)

674
00:44:54,275 --> 00:44:57,653
-Calculation complete.
-Same software. Different face.

675
00:44:57,778 --> 00:45:01,908
Hey. 400 years in four seconds!
We may have had our differences,

676
00:45:01,991 --> 00:45:03,993
which is frankly odd,
in the circumstances,

677
00:45:04,118 --> 00:45:07,788
but I tell you what, boys,
we are incredibly clever.

678
00:45:12,793 --> 00:45:15,671
-How did you do that?
-It wasn't locked.

679
00:45:15,796 --> 00:45:17,465
Right.

680
00:45:18,674 --> 00:45:22,011
-So they're both you, then, yeah?
-Yes. You've met them before.

681
00:45:22,136 --> 00:45:24,805
-Don't you remember?
-A bit. Nice suit.

682
00:45:25,473 --> 00:45:27,683
-Thanks.
-Hang on.

683
00:45:27,808 --> 00:45:31,020
Three of you in one cell, and
none of you thought to try the door?

684
00:45:31,145 --> 00:45:34,190
-Should have been locked.
-Yes, exactly. Why wasn't it locked?

685
00:45:34,315 --> 00:45:37,777
Because I was fascinated to see
what you would do upon escaping.

686
00:45:37,860 --> 00:45:40,655
I understand you're rather fond
of this world.

687
00:45:40,738 --> 00:45:43,658
It's time, I think, you saw
what's going to happen to it.

688
00:46:05,346 --> 00:46:06,931
(GROAN)

689
00:46:16,440 --> 00:46:18,734
Kate! Goodness,
you're not actually dead.

690
00:46:18,859 --> 00:46:20,861
Oh, that's tremendous news.

691
00:46:21,529 --> 00:46:22,530
(GROANS)

692
00:46:22,613 --> 00:46:25,741
Those creatures,
they turn themselves into copies.

693
00:46:25,866 --> 00:46:28,160
Maybe they need to
keep the original alive.

694
00:46:28,244 --> 00:46:31,372
-Refresh the image, so to speak.
-Oh. Where did they go?

695
00:46:31,455 --> 00:46:34,542
I don't know. Hang on, yes, I do.
The Tower.

696
00:46:34,625 --> 00:46:38,921
If those creatures have got access
to the Black Archive,

697
00:46:39,046 --> 00:46:41,215
we may just have lost control
of the planet.

698
00:46:43,634 --> 00:46:46,095
The Zygons lost their own world.

699
00:46:46,220 --> 00:46:48,931
It burned in the first days
of the Time War.

700
00:46:50,474 --> 00:46:52,601
A new home is required.

701
00:46:53,811 --> 00:46:58,232
-CLARA: So they want this one?
-Not yet. Far too primitive.

702
00:46:58,899 --> 00:47:01,610
Zygons are used to
a certain level of comfort.

703
00:47:01,736 --> 00:47:03,904
ZYGON: Commander.

704
00:47:05,489 --> 00:47:10,202
-Why are these creatures here?
-Because I say they should be.

705
00:47:10,286 --> 00:47:12,955
It is time you, too, were translated.

706
00:47:13,080 --> 00:47:14,582
(SNARLS)

707
00:47:15,583 --> 00:47:19,503
Observe this.
I believe you will find it fascinating.

708
00:47:29,972 --> 00:47:33,142
That's him. That's the Zygon,
in the picture, now.

709
00:47:33,267 --> 00:47:35,644
OLD DOCTOR: It's not a picture.
It's a Stasis Cube.

710
00:47:35,770 --> 00:47:39,899
Time Lord art.
Frozen instants in time.

711
00:47:39,982 --> 00:47:43,652
Bigger on the inside,
but could be deployed as...

712
00:47:43,778 --> 00:47:47,365
Suspended animation.
Oh, that's very good.

713
00:47:48,449 --> 00:47:50,659
The Zygons all pop inside the pictures,
wait a few centuries

714
00:47:50,785 --> 00:47:53,662
till the planet's a bit more interesting
and then out they come.

715
00:47:53,788 --> 00:47:56,499
You see, Clara? They're stored in
the paintings in the Under-Gallery

716
00:47:56,624 --> 00:48:00,669
like Cup-a-Soups, except you add time,
if you can picture that.

717
00:48:00,795 --> 00:48:03,589
Nobody can picture that.
Forget I said "Cup-a-Soups".

718
00:48:03,672 --> 00:48:06,008
And now the world is worth conquering.

719
00:48:06,133 --> 00:48:09,512
CLARA: So the Zygons
are invading the future from the past?

720
00:48:09,637 --> 00:48:11,722
Exactly.

721
00:48:13,140 --> 00:48:16,352
And do you know why
I know that you're a fake?

722
00:48:16,477 --> 00:48:19,105
Because you're such a bad copy.

723
00:48:19,188 --> 00:48:22,191
It's not just the smell,
or the unconvincing hair,

724
00:48:22,316 --> 00:48:25,277
or the atrocious teeth, or the eyes
just a bit too close together,

725
00:48:25,361 --> 00:48:28,531
or the breath that could stun a horse.

726
00:48:28,656 --> 00:48:30,825
It's because my Elizabeth,
the real Elizabeth,

727
00:48:30,908 --> 00:48:33,828
would never be stupid enough
to reveal her own plan.

728
00:48:34,745 --> 00:48:36,831
Honestly, why would you do that?

729
00:48:37,665 --> 00:48:41,669
Because it's not my plan.
And I am the real Elizabeth.

730
00:48:43,045 --> 00:48:45,798
Okay, so,

731
00:48:45,881 --> 00:48:49,051
backtracking a moment just to lend
some context to my earlier remarks...

732
00:48:49,218 --> 00:48:54,390
My twin is dead in the forest.
I am accustomed to taking precautions.

733
00:48:54,515 --> 00:48:57,393
These Zygon creatures never even
considered that it was me who survived,

734
00:48:57,518 --> 00:49:01,856
rather than their own commander.
The arrogance that typifies their kind.

735
00:49:01,939 --> 00:49:02,898
Zygons?

736
00:49:03,023 --> 00:49:05,568
-Men.
-And you actually killed one of them?

737
00:49:05,693 --> 00:49:08,237
I may have the body
of a weak and feeble woman,

738
00:49:08,362 --> 00:49:10,865
but at the time, so did the Zygon.

739
00:49:10,948 --> 00:49:13,492
The future of my kingdom
is imperilled.

740
00:49:13,576 --> 00:49:15,744
Doctor, can I rely on your service?

741
00:49:15,870 --> 00:49:19,039
-I'm going to need my Tardis.
-It has been procured already.

742
00:49:19,915 --> 00:49:23,377
But first, my love,
you have a promise to keep.

743
00:49:27,298 --> 00:49:30,718
PRIEST: I now pronounce you
man and wife.

744
00:49:30,801 --> 00:49:33,429
- (CLARA WHOOPS)
-You may kiss the bride.

745
00:49:38,893 --> 00:49:43,814
-Is there a lot of this in the future?
-It does start to happen, yeah.

746
00:49:45,941 --> 00:49:49,612
-Godspeed, my love.
-I will be right back.

747
00:49:56,410 --> 00:49:57,828
Wooh!

748
00:49:59,914 --> 00:50:02,416
ELEVENTH DOCTOR: Right then,
back to the future.

749
00:50:05,503 --> 00:50:07,254
You've let this place go a bit.

750
00:50:07,338 --> 00:50:10,049
Ah, it's his grunge phase.
He grows out of it.

751
00:50:10,132 --> 00:50:12,384
Don't you listen to them.

752
00:50:12,468 --> 00:50:15,596
-Oh!
-The desktop is glitching.

753
00:50:16,347 --> 00:50:19,475
Three of us from different time zones.
It's trying to compensate.

754
00:50:19,600 --> 00:50:22,311
Hey, look. The round things.

755
00:50:22,436 --> 00:50:25,648
-I love the round things.
-What are the round things?

756
00:50:25,773 --> 00:50:29,652
-No idea.
-Oh, dear, the friction contrafibulator!

757
00:50:29,777 --> 00:50:32,279
Ha! There, stabilised.

758
00:50:34,448 --> 00:50:37,368
Oh, you've redecorated.
I don't like it.

759
00:50:37,993 --> 00:50:40,996
Oh, yeah? Oh, you never do. Listen.

760
00:50:41,121 --> 00:50:43,624
We're going to the National Gallery.
The Zygons are underneath it.

761
00:50:43,707 --> 00:50:46,669
No, UNIT HQ. They followed us there.
In the Black Archive.

762
00:50:49,713 --> 00:50:52,383
Okay, so you've heard of that, then.

763
00:50:54,885 --> 00:50:57,555
The equipment here is phenomenal.

764
00:50:57,638 --> 00:51:00,766
The humans don't realise
what half this stuff does.

765
00:51:00,849 --> 00:51:03,310
We could conquer their world in a day.

766
00:51:03,394 --> 00:51:07,523
ZYGON: We were fortunate, then,
in our choice of duplicate.

767
00:51:07,648 --> 00:51:10,985
If I were human,
I'd say it was Christmas.

768
00:51:11,694 --> 00:51:15,531
No, I'm afraid you wouldn't.
We're not armed. You may relax.

769
00:51:15,656 --> 00:51:18,867
ZYGON: We are armed. You may not.

770
00:51:18,993 --> 00:51:22,830
Lock the door.
I'm afraid we can't be interrupted.

771
00:51:23,581 --> 00:51:29,253
-You don't mind if I get comfortable?
-You don't mind if I do?

772
00:51:37,052 --> 00:51:40,889
You'll realise there are protocols
protecting this place. Osgood?

773
00:51:41,015 --> 00:51:43,017
In the event of alien incursion,
the contents of this room

774
00:51:43,267 --> 00:51:45,477
are deemed so dangerous,
it will self-destruct in...

775
00:51:45,561 --> 00:51:47,688
-Five minutes.
-(WARNING BLEEP)

776
00:51:49,189 --> 00:51:51,900
There's a nuclear warhead
20 feet beneath us.

777
00:51:52,026 --> 00:51:53,861
Are you sitting comfortably?

778
00:51:53,944 --> 00:51:57,740
-You would destroy London?
-To save the world? Yes, I would.

779
00:51:57,865 --> 00:52:00,534
-You're bluffing.
-You really think so?

780
00:52:00,618 --> 00:52:02,077
Somewhere in your memory
is @ man called

781
00:52:02,202 --> 00:52:04,705
Brigadier Alistair Gordon
Lethbridge-Stewart.

782
00:52:05,372 --> 00:52:06,999
I am his daughter.

783
00:52:07,082 --> 00:52:09,209
ELEVENTH DOCTOR: Science leads, Kate.
Is that what you meant?

784
00:52:09,293 --> 00:52:11,837
-Is that what your father meant?
-Doctor?

785
00:52:11,920 --> 00:52:15,591
Space-time telegraph, Kate.
A gift from me to your father.

786
00:52:15,716 --> 00:52:19,261
Hotline straight to the Tardis.
I know about the Black Archive,

787
00:52:19,386 --> 00:52:22,431
and I know about the security protocol.
Kate, please...

788
00:52:22,556 --> 00:52:26,268
Please tell me you are not about to
do something unbelievably stupid.

789
00:52:26,393 --> 00:52:29,438
-I'm sorry, Doctor. Switch it off.
-Not as sorry as you will be.

790
00:52:29,563 --> 00:52:32,900
This is not a decision
you will ever be able to live with!

791
00:52:35,653 --> 00:52:37,905
(TARDIS JUDDERING)

792
00:52:38,072 --> 00:52:39,239
Kate!

793
00:52:39,323 --> 00:52:42,409
Argh! We're trying to bring
the Tardis in. Why can't we land?

794
00:52:42,618 --> 00:52:46,246
-I said switch it off.
-No, Kate, please, just listen to me!

795
00:52:46,330 --> 00:52:48,749
(TELEGRAPH CUTS OUT)

796
00:52:52,086 --> 00:52:55,297
-Tower of London. Totally Tardis-proof.
-CLARA: How can they do that?

797
00:52:55,422 --> 00:52:58,926
Alien technology, plus human stupidity.
Trust me, it's unbeatable.

798
00:52:59,009 --> 00:53:01,095
We don't need to land.

799
00:53:02,638 --> 00:53:05,224
Yeah, we do, a tiny bit.
Try and keep up.

800
00:53:05,307 --> 00:53:10,270
No, we don't. We don't.
There is another way.

801
00:53:13,482 --> 00:53:15,609
"Cup-a-Soup".

802
00:53:18,821 --> 00:53:20,781
What is Cup-a-Soup?

803
00:53:22,950 --> 00:53:25,619
-What happened?
-Easier to show you.

804
00:53:29,373 --> 00:53:31,458
(PHONE RINGS)

805
00:53:33,794 --> 00:53:34,962
McGillop.

806
00:53:35,045 --> 00:53:38,298
Take a look at your phone
and confirm who you're talking to.

807
00:53:42,302 --> 00:53:44,346
But that's not possible.
I was just...

808
00:53:44,471 --> 00:53:47,349
You were just talking to me. I know.
I'm a time-traveller. Figure it out.

809
00:53:47,474 --> 00:53:50,394
I need you to send the Gallifrey Falls
painting to the Black Archive.

810
00:53:50,477 --> 00:53:52,312
-Understood?
-Understood, sir,

811
00:53:52,521 --> 00:53:55,649
but why would I take it there?

812
00:53:55,733 --> 00:53:58,610
ALIEN KATE: One word from you
would cancel the countdown.

813
00:53:58,694 --> 00:54:01,029
-Quite so.
-It's keyed to your voice print.

814
00:54:01,155 --> 00:54:03,282
-And mine alone.
-Not any more.

815
00:54:03,365 --> 00:54:05,325
-Cancel the detonation.
-Countermanded.

816
00:54:05,409 --> 00:54:08,162
-Cancel the detonation.
-Countermanded!

817
00:54:08,245 --> 00:54:12,875
-We only have to agree to live.
-Sadly, we can only agree to die.

818
00:54:13,000 --> 00:54:16,211
Please, Doctor, please save us.

819
00:54:16,336 --> 00:54:19,673
Please save us, please save us,
please save us, please save us...

820
00:54:31,351 --> 00:54:33,562
Exterminate!

821
00:54:34,354 --> 00:54:36,190
(DALEK SCREAMING)

822
00:55:03,467 --> 00:55:05,761
-Hello.
-I'm the Doctor.

823
00:55:05,886 --> 00:55:08,055
Sorry about the Dalek.

824
00:55:08,555 --> 00:55:12,851
-Also the showing-off.
-Kate Lethbridge-Stewart,

825
00:55:12,935 --> 00:55:15,437
what in the name of sanity
are you doing?

826
00:55:15,562 --> 00:55:18,065
The countdown can only be halted
at my personal command.

827
00:55:18,148 --> 00:55:21,401
-There's nothing you can do.
-Except make you both agree to halt it.

828
00:55:21,485 --> 00:55:22,778
Not even for three of you.

829
00:55:22,903 --> 00:55:25,113
You're about to murder
millions of people.

830
00:55:25,239 --> 00:55:29,409
To save billions. How many times
have you made that calculation?

831
00:55:29,493 --> 00:55:32,329
Once. It turned me into
the man I am now.

832
00:55:33,914 --> 00:55:36,917
Not even sure who that is any more.
You tell yourself it's justified,

833
00:55:37,000 --> 00:55:40,754
but it's a lie,
because what I did that day was wrong.

834
00:55:40,838 --> 00:55:44,758
Just wrong.
And because I got it wrong,

835
00:55:44,842 --> 00:55:49,638
I'm going to make you get it right.

836
00:55:50,264 --> 00:55:51,974
How?

837
00:55:52,850 --> 00:55:55,102
Any second now,
you're going to stop that countdown.

838
00:55:55,185 --> 00:55:56,270
Both of you, together.

839
00:55:56,353 --> 00:55:59,147
And then you're going to negotiate
the most perfect treaty of all time.

840
00:55:59,273 --> 00:56:00,816
Safeguards all round.
Completely fair on both sides.

841
00:56:00,941 --> 00:56:04,486
-And the key to perfect negotiation...
-...is not knowing what side you're on.

842
00:56:05,487 --> 00:56:09,324
So, for the next few hours,
until we decide to let you out...

843
00:56:09,449 --> 00:56:11,493
No one in this room
will be able to remember

844
00:56:11,618 --> 00:56:14,997
if they're human or a Zygon.
Whoops-a-daisy!

845
00:56:15,122 --> 00:56:16,957
(SCREWDRIVER HUMMING)

846
00:56:25,966 --> 00:56:28,719
BOTH: Cancel the detonation!

847
00:56:30,137 --> 00:56:31,972
Peace in our time.

848
00:56:42,649 --> 00:56:45,861
It's funny, isn't it? If I'm a Zygon,
then my clothes must be Zygon too.

849
00:56:45,986 --> 00:56:48,989
So, what happens if I lose a shoe
or something?

850
00:56:49,823 --> 00:56:51,867
(COUGHS)

851
00:57:22,439 --> 00:57:23,857
Hello.

852
00:57:24,775 --> 00:57:25,734
Hello.

853
00:57:25,859 --> 00:57:27,945
I'm Clara.
We haven't really met yet.

854
00:57:28,570 --> 00:57:30,697
I look forward to it.

855
00:57:34,534 --> 00:57:37,621
-Is there a problem?
-The Doctor, my...

856
00:57:39,373 --> 00:57:43,418
My Doctor... He's always talking about
the day he did it.

857
00:57:45,212 --> 00:57:47,547
The day he wiped out the Time Lords
to stop the war.

858
00:57:47,756 --> 00:57:50,717
-One would.
-CLARA: You wouldn't.

859
00:57:52,886 --> 00:57:55,931
'Cause you haven't done it yet.
It's still in your future.

860
00:57:58,767 --> 00:58:01,478
-You're very sure of yourself.
-He regrets it.

861
00:58:03,271 --> 00:58:06,233
I see it in his eyes every day.
He'd do anything to change it.

862
00:58:06,900 --> 00:58:09,236
Including saving all these people?

863
00:58:11,113 --> 00:58:14,491
How many worlds
has his regret saved, do you think?

864
00:58:14,783 --> 00:58:20,580
Look over there. Humans and Zygons,
working together in peace.

865
00:58:22,499 --> 00:58:24,084
How did you know?

866
00:58:24,835 --> 00:58:26,420
Your eyes.

867
00:58:28,088 --> 00:58:29,798
You're so much younger.

868
00:58:32,342 --> 00:58:34,636
Then, all things considered,

869
00:58:36,263 --> 00:58:38,432
it's time I grew up.

870
00:58:41,935 --> 00:58:44,771
I've seen all I needed.

871
00:58:45,689 --> 00:58:47,774
The moment has come.

872
00:58:52,863 --> 00:58:55,824
-I'm ready.
-ROSE: I know you are.

873
00:58:57,951 --> 00:58:59,411
Who's there?

874
00:58:59,494 --> 00:59:01,830
Who are you talking to?

875
00:59:15,385 --> 00:59:18,305
ROSE: Well, you wanted
a big red button.

876
00:59:18,472 --> 00:59:22,851
One big bang. No more Time Lords,

877
00:59:22,976 --> 00:59:25,020
no more Daleks.

878
00:59:25,145 --> 00:59:27,189
Are you sure?

879
00:59:28,482 --> 00:59:30,567
I was sure when I came in here.

880
00:59:31,735 --> 00:59:35,530
-There is no other way.
-You've seen the men you will become.

881
00:59:35,655 --> 00:59:39,242
Those men. Extraordinary.

882
00:59:40,410 --> 00:59:43,747
-They were you.
-No.

883
00:59:44,915 --> 00:59:47,292
They are the Doctor.

884
00:59:47,375 --> 00:59:49,711
-You're the Doctor, too.
-No.

885
00:59:51,713 --> 00:59:54,424
Great men are forged in fire.

886
00:59:56,009 --> 00:59:58,845
It is the privilege of lesser men
to light the flame.

887
01:00:04,059 --> 01:00:06,520
Whatever the cost.

888
01:00:06,603 --> 01:00:08,522
(ECHOING LAUGHTER)

889
01:00:14,694 --> 01:00:16,488
You know the sound the Tardis makes?

890
01:00:16,571 --> 01:00:19,533
That wheezing groaning?

891
01:00:21,284 --> 01:00:24,955
That sound brings hope
wherever it goes.

892
01:00:25,872 --> 01:00:29,584
Yes. Yes, I like to think it does.

893
01:00:29,709 --> 01:00:32,045
To anyone who hears it, Doctor.

894
01:00:33,755 --> 01:00:35,423
Anyone,

895
01:00:35,549 --> 01:00:37,509
however lost.

896
01:00:37,592 --> 01:00:39,761
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

897
01:00:39,886 --> 01:00:42,389
Even you.

898
01:01:05,245 --> 01:01:07,414
(WHISPERS) I told you
he hasn't done it yet.

899
01:01:07,831 --> 01:01:11,293
Go away, now. All of you.
This is for me.

900
01:01:14,087 --> 01:01:16,798
These events should be time-locked.
We shouldn't even be here.

901
01:01:16,923 --> 01:01:18,758
So something let us through.

902
01:01:19,342 --> 01:01:22,804
-You clever boys.
-Go back.

903
01:01:23,930 --> 01:01:26,099
Go back to your lives.

904
01:01:26,975 --> 01:01:29,978
Go and be the Doctor
that I could never be.

905
01:01:30,937 --> 01:01:34,482
Make it worthwhile.

906
01:01:37,360 --> 01:01:40,780
TENTH DOCTOR: All those years
burying you in my memory.

907
01:01:41,781 --> 01:01:44,117
ELEVENTH DOCTOR:
Pretending you didn't exist.

908
01:01:44,701 --> 01:01:47,287
Keeping you a secret,
even from myself.

909
01:01:48,788 --> 01:01:50,665
TENTH DOCTOR:
Pretending you weren't the Doctor,

910
01:01:50,790 --> 01:01:53,335
when you were the Doctor
more than anybody else.

911
01:01:53,460 --> 01:01:58,131
You were the Doctor on the day
it wasn't possible to get it right.

912
01:02:02,802 --> 01:02:04,971
But this time,

913
01:02:06,723 --> 01:02:08,808
you don't have to do it alone.

914
01:02:13,563 --> 01:02:15,649
Thank you.

915
01:02:18,318 --> 01:02:22,239
What we do today
is not out of fear or hatred.

916
01:02:23,907 --> 01:02:26,368
It is done because
there is no other way.

917
01:02:28,495 --> 01:02:30,664
And it is done in the name
of the many lives

918
01:02:30,747 --> 01:02:32,832
we are failing to save.

919
01:02:44,678 --> 01:02:46,179
What?

920
01:02:47,347 --> 01:02:49,349
What is it? What?

921
01:02:49,432 --> 01:02:51,851
-Nothing.
-No.

922
01:02:52,519 --> 01:02:54,104
Something. Tell me.

923
01:02:55,522 --> 01:02:58,525
You told me you wiped out
your own people. I just...

924
01:03:00,277 --> 01:03:03,655
I never pictured you doing it.
That's all.

925
01:03:03,738 --> 01:03:05,365
Take a closer look.

926
01:03:11,579 --> 01:03:14,541
CLARA: What's happening?
OLD DOCTOR: Nothing.

927
01:03:14,624 --> 01:03:16,710
It's a projection.

928
01:03:17,877 --> 01:03:20,714
ROSE: It's the reality around you.

929
01:03:22,716 --> 01:03:25,427
(ECHOING LAUGHTER)

930
01:03:25,552 --> 01:03:27,595
(ECHOING SCREAM)

931
01:03:33,643 --> 01:03:36,271
These are the people
you're going to burn?

932
01:03:40,942 --> 01:03:43,278
There isn't anything we can do.

933
01:03:43,403 --> 01:03:46,614
You're right. There isn't another way.
There never was.

934
01:03:46,740 --> 01:03:51,036
Either I destroy my own people,
or let the universe burn.

935
01:03:51,119 --> 01:03:55,081
Look at you. The three of you.

936
01:03:56,333 --> 01:03:57,917
The warrior. The hero.

937
01:03:59,252 --> 01:04:00,670
And you.

938
01:04:05,800 --> 01:04:07,385
And what am I?

939
01:04:07,469 --> 01:04:09,471
-Have you really forgotten?
-Yes.

940
01:04:10,138 --> 01:04:12,098
Maybe, yes.

941
01:04:12,932 --> 01:04:17,604
We've got enough warriors.
Any old idiot can be a hero.

942
01:04:18,355 --> 01:04:20,440
(DISTANT SIRENS)

943
01:04:21,358 --> 01:04:23,443
Then what do I do?

944
01:04:27,197 --> 01:04:29,366
What you've always done.

945
01:04:32,952 --> 01:04:34,621
Be a Doctor.

946
01:04:44,506 --> 01:04:48,468
CLARA: You told me the name you chose
was a promise. What was the promise?

947
01:04:50,053 --> 01:04:52,305
Never cruel or cowardly.

948
01:04:54,808 --> 01:04:58,311
Never give up. Never give in.

949
01:05:21,751 --> 01:05:25,672
You're not actually suggesting that
we change our own personal history?

950
01:05:25,755 --> 01:05:28,550
We change history all the time.

951
01:05:28,675 --> 01:05:31,719
-I'm suggesting something far worse.
-What, exactly?

952
01:05:34,848 --> 01:05:38,518
Gentlemen, I have had 400 years

953
01:05:38,601 --> 01:05:40,854
to think about this.

954
01:05:42,397 --> 01:05:45,066
I've changed my mind.

955
01:05:50,029 --> 01:05:53,700
There's still a billion billion Daleks
up there, attacking.

956
01:05:53,783 --> 01:05:55,535
Yep, there is. There is. But...

957
01:05:55,618 --> 01:05:59,205
there's something
those billion billion Daleks don't know.

958
01:05:59,289 --> 01:06:01,541
'Cause if they did,
they'd probably send for reinforcements.

959
01:06:01,624 --> 01:06:04,919
-What? What don't they know?
-This time, there's three of us.

960
01:06:05,044 --> 01:06:06,754
Oh!

961
01:06:06,880 --> 01:06:11,968
Oh, yes, that is good!
That is brilliant.

962
01:06:12,218 --> 01:06:15,430
Oh! Oh, I'm getting that too!
That is brilliant!

963
01:06:16,931 --> 01:06:19,934
I've been thinking about it
for centuries.

964
01:06:20,059 --> 01:06:22,604
She didn't just show me
any old future.

965
01:06:22,729 --> 01:06:26,024
She told me exactly the future
I needed to see!

966
01:06:26,107 --> 01:06:27,859
-Now you're getting it.
-Eh?

967
01:06:27,942 --> 01:06:32,780
-Bad Wolf Girl, I could kiss you.
-(SARCASTIC) Yup, that's gonna happen.

968
01:06:32,906 --> 01:06:34,866
Sorry, did you just say "Bad Wolf"?

969
01:06:34,949 --> 01:06:37,202
So, what are we doing?
What's the plan?

970
01:06:37,285 --> 01:06:40,788
The Dalek fleets are surrounding
Gallifrey, firing on it constantly.

971
01:06:40,914 --> 01:06:43,917
The Sky Trench is holding.
But what if the whole planet

972
01:06:44,000 --> 01:06:46,377
-just disappeared?
-Tiny bit of an ask.

973
01:06:46,461 --> 01:06:47,921
The Daleks would be firing
on each other.

974
01:06:48,004 --> 01:06:50,131
They'd destroy themselves
in their own crossfire.

975
01:06:50,256 --> 01:06:52,467
Gallifrey will be gone.
The Daleks will be destroyed.

976
01:06:52,592 --> 01:06:54,636
And it would look
to the rest of the universe

977
01:06:54,761 --> 01:06:57,472
-as if they'd annihilated each other.
-But where would Gallifrey be?

978
01:06:57,597 --> 01:06:59,265
Frozen.

979
01:06:59,933 --> 01:07:02,393
Frozen in an instant of time,

980
01:07:02,477 --> 01:07:04,479
safe and hidden away.

981
01:07:04,604 --> 01:07:07,941
-Exactly.
-Like a painting.

982
01:07:17,825 --> 01:07:19,244
ANDROGAR: Another one.

983
01:07:19,327 --> 01:07:20,662
GENERAL: Are you sure the message
is from him?

984
01:07:20,787 --> 01:07:22,539
-Oh, yes.
-Why would he do that?

985
01:07:24,999 --> 01:07:27,710
What's the mad fool
talking about now?

986
01:07:27,835 --> 01:07:30,630
ELEVENTH DOCTOR: Hello.
Hello, Gallifrey High Command.

987
01:07:30,713 --> 01:07:32,966
- This is the Doctor speaking.
-TENTH DOCTOR: Hello!

988
01:07:33,049 --> 01:07:36,135
-Also the Doctor. Can you hear me?
-OLD DOCTOR: Also the Doctor.

989
01:07:36,219 --> 01:07:37,303
Standing ready.

990
01:07:37,387 --> 01:07:39,806
Dear God. Three of them.

991
01:07:39,889 --> 01:07:42,308
All my worst nightmares at once.

992
01:07:42,392 --> 01:07:44,477
General, we have a plan.

993
01:07:44,561 --> 01:07:47,146
We should point out at this moment
it is a fairly terrible plan,

994
01:07:47,230 --> 01:07:49,983
-and almost certainly won't work.
- I was happy with "fairly terrible.”

995
01:07:50,066 --> 01:07:51,693
Sorry, I was just thinking aloud.

996
01:07:51,818 --> 01:07:54,571
We are flying our three Tardises
into your lower atmosphere.

997
01:07:56,489 --> 01:07:59,576
We're positioned at equidistant
intervals around the globe.

998
01:07:59,701 --> 01:08:01,160
"Equidistant.” So grown-up.

999
01:08:03,830 --> 01:08:06,833
Just about ready to do it.

1000
01:08:06,916 --> 01:08:10,878
-GENERAL: Ready to do what?
-We're going to freeze Gallifrey.

1001
01:08:11,004 --> 01:08:12,922
I'm sorry? What?

1002
01:08:13,047 --> 01:08:15,383
Using our Tardises,
we're gonna freeze Gallifrey

1003
01:08:15,508 --> 01:08:19,012
-in a single moment in time.
-You know, like those Stasis Cubes?

1004
01:08:19,095 --> 01:08:23,683
Single moment in time,
held in a parallel pocket universe.

1005
01:08:23,766 --> 01:08:25,852
Except we're going to do it
to a whole planet.

1006
01:08:25,935 --> 01:08:28,354
-And all the people on it.
-What?

1007
01:08:28,438 --> 01:08:31,190
Even if that were possible,
which it isn't,

1008
01:08:31,274 --> 01:08:34,235
-why would you do such a thing?
-Because the alternative is burning.

1009
01:08:34,360 --> 01:08:38,573
-And I've seen that.
-And I never want to see it again.

1010
01:08:39,449 --> 01:08:42,785
We'd be lost in another universe,

1011
01:08:43,620 --> 01:08:47,457
frozen in a single moment.
We'd have nothing.

1012
01:08:47,624 --> 01:08:49,417
You would have hope.

1013
01:08:49,542 --> 01:08:51,919
And right now, that is
exactly what you don't have.

1014
01:08:52,045 --> 01:08:55,381
It's delusional.
Why, the calculations alone

1015
01:08:55,465 --> 01:08:58,301
would take hundreds of years.

1016
01:08:58,426 --> 01:09:00,970
-Oh, hundreds and hundreds.
-But don't worry.

1017
01:09:01,095 --> 01:09:03,431
I started a very long time ago.

1018
01:09:06,893 --> 01:09:10,188
Warning the War Council of Gallifrey.
This is the Doctor.

1019
01:09:10,271 --> 01:09:14,067
ELEVENTH DOCTOR: You might say
I've been doing this all my lives.

1020
01:09:14,984 --> 01:09:16,069
-Good luck
-Stand by.

1021
01:09:16,152 --> 01:09:17,904
-Ready.
-Commencing calculations.

1022
01:09:17,987 --> 01:09:19,364
Soon be there.

1023
01:09:19,447 --> 01:09:21,949
Across the boundaries
that divide one universe from another.

1024
01:09:22,075 --> 01:09:25,912
-We'll lock onto its coordinates.
-And for my next trick...

1025
01:09:26,329 --> 01:09:29,582
I didn't know when I was well off.
All twelve of them!

1026
01:09:29,666 --> 01:09:32,168
No, sir. Argh!

1027
01:09:32,251 --> 01:09:33,961
All thirteen!

1028
01:09:39,175 --> 01:09:41,844
ANDROGAR: Sir, the Daleks know
that something is happening.

1029
01:09:41,928 --> 01:09:43,930
They're increasing their firepower.

1030
01:09:52,021 --> 01:09:55,817
Do it, Doctor. Just do it.

1031
01:09:57,360 --> 01:09:59,487
GENERAL: Do it!

1032
01:10:00,863 --> 01:10:02,031
Okay.

1033
01:10:02,156 --> 01:10:04,784
ELEVENTH DOCTOR:
Gentlemen, we're ready.

1034
01:10:07,620 --> 01:10:10,331
(YELLS) Geronimo!

1035
01:10:11,374 --> 01:10:14,961
-Allons-y!
-Oh, for God's sake.

1036
01:10:15,044 --> 01:10:17,338
Gallifrey stands!

1037
01:10:35,064 --> 01:10:38,192
I don't suppose we'll ever know
if we actually succeeded.

1038
01:10:39,527 --> 01:10:43,156
But at worst,
we failed doing the right thing,

1039
01:10:43,239 --> 01:10:46,743
as opposed to succeeding
in doing the wrong.

1040
01:10:48,536 --> 01:10:50,580
Life and soul, you are.

1041
01:10:52,582 --> 01:10:55,168
What is it actually called?

1042
01:10:56,419 --> 01:10:58,671
Well, there's some debate.

1043
01:10:58,755 --> 01:11:02,216
Either No More
or Gallifrey Falls.

1044
01:11:02,341 --> 01:11:05,845
-Not very encouraging.
-How did it get here?

1045
01:11:07,013 --> 01:11:09,056
No idea.

1046
01:11:09,932 --> 01:11:12,185
There's always something
we don't know, isn't there?

1047
01:11:12,268 --> 01:11:15,062
OLD DOCTOR:
I should certainly hope so.

1048
01:11:15,188 --> 01:11:18,608
Well, gentlemen,
it has been an honour

1049
01:11:18,733 --> 01:11:20,526
and a privilege.

1050
01:11:20,610 --> 01:11:23,070
-Likewise.
-Doctor.

1051
01:11:25,615 --> 01:11:29,035
And if I grow to be
half the man that you are,

1052
01:11:29,118 --> 01:11:33,289
Clara Oswald,
I shall be happy indeed.

1053
01:11:33,414 --> 01:11:36,584
-That's right. Aim high.
-(BOTH CHUCKLE)

1054
01:11:41,756 --> 01:11:44,300
I won't remember this, will I?

1055
01:11:44,884 --> 01:11:49,388
The time streams are out of sync.
You can't retain it, no.

1056
01:11:49,472 --> 01:11:52,809
So I won't remember
that I tried to save Gallifrey,

1057
01:11:52,934 --> 01:11:55,144
rather than burn it.

1058
01:11:56,646 --> 01:11:58,981
And I have to live with that.

1059
01:12:00,233 --> 01:12:03,402
But for now, for this moment,

1060
01:12:04,612 --> 01:12:06,781
I am the Doctor again.

1061
01:12:08,115 --> 01:12:09,826
Thank you.

1062
01:12:14,413 --> 01:12:15,998
Which one is mine?

1063
01:12:18,918 --> 01:12:19,919
Ha!

1064
01:12:26,759 --> 01:12:28,928
(WHOOSHING)

1065
01:12:33,850 --> 01:12:36,310
Oh, yes.

1066
01:12:36,477 --> 01:12:39,313
Of course, it makes sense.

1067
01:12:40,773 --> 01:12:42,859
Wearing a bit thin.

1068
01:12:45,862 --> 01:12:49,824
I hope the ears are
a bit less conspicuous this time.

1069
01:13:06,215 --> 01:13:08,718
I won't remember, either,
so you might as well tell me.

1070
01:13:10,803 --> 01:13:11,804
Tell you what?

1071
01:13:11,888 --> 01:13:14,557
Where it is we're going
that you don't want to talk about.

1072
01:13:20,688 --> 01:13:23,190
I saw Trenzalore,

1073
01:13:23,316 --> 01:13:25,401
where we're buried.

1074
01:13:26,360 --> 01:13:28,529
We die in battle, among millions.

1075
01:13:30,573 --> 01:13:33,034
-That's not how it's supposed to be.
-That's how the story ends.

1076
01:13:33,159 --> 01:13:35,328
Nothing we can do about it.

1077
01:13:36,245 --> 01:13:38,414
Trenzalore is where you're going.

1078
01:13:41,042 --> 01:13:43,419
Oh, never say "nothing".

1079
01:13:43,544 --> 01:13:45,171
Anyway,

1080
01:13:46,088 --> 01:13:49,091
good to know my future
is in safe hands.

1081
01:13:50,718 --> 01:13:54,889
-Keep a tight hold on it, Clara.
-Mm. On it.

1082
01:14:01,771 --> 01:14:03,356
Trenzalore.

1083
01:14:03,439 --> 01:14:06,275
We need a new destination, because...

1084
01:14:08,194 --> 01:14:10,613
I don't wanna go.

1085
01:14:19,455 --> 01:14:21,624
He always says that.

1086
01:14:31,884 --> 01:14:34,053
Need a moment alone with your painting?

1087
01:14:34,637 --> 01:14:37,890
-How did you know?
-Those big sad eyes.

1088
01:14:45,731 --> 01:14:47,817
I always know.

1089
01:14:49,485 --> 01:14:52,029
Oh, by the way, there was an old man
looking for you.

1090
01:14:52,113 --> 01:14:54,323
I think it was the curator.

1091
01:15:04,500 --> 01:15:06,877
I could be a curator.

1092
01:15:06,961 --> 01:15:11,924
I'd be great at curating.
I'd be the Great Curator. (CHUCKLES)

1093
01:15:12,008 --> 01:15:14,343
I could retire, and do that.

1094
01:15:15,177 --> 01:15:18,347
I could retire,
and be the curator of this place.

1095
01:15:20,599 --> 01:15:23,519
CURATOR:
You know, I really think you might.

1096
01:15:46,042 --> 01:15:49,795
-I never forget a face.
-I know you don't.

1097
01:15:49,879 --> 01:15:53,674
And in years to come, you might
find yourself revisiting a few.

1098
01:15:53,799 --> 01:15:56,385
But just the old favourites, eh?

1099
01:16:00,347 --> 01:16:02,975
You were curious
about this painting, I think?

1100
01:16:03,059 --> 01:16:06,145
I acquired it
in remarkable circumstances.

1101
01:16:06,228 --> 01:16:10,399
-What do you make of the title?
-Well, which title? There's two.

1102
01:16:12,193 --> 01:16:14,320
No More,

1103
01:16:14,403 --> 01:16:16,405
and Gallifrey Falls.

1104
01:16:16,530 --> 01:16:19,075
No, you see,
that's where everybody's wrong.

1105
01:16:19,200 --> 01:16:21,827
It's all one title.

1106
01:16:21,911 --> 01:16:25,331
Gallifrey Falls No More.

1107
01:16:26,582 --> 01:16:29,668
Now, what would you think
that means, eh?

1108
01:16:32,505 --> 01:16:35,341
That Gallifrey didn't fall.

1109
01:16:35,424 --> 01:16:38,260
It worked? It's still out there?

1110
01:16:38,385 --> 01:16:40,846
I'm only a humble curator.
I'm sure I wouldn't know.

1111
01:16:40,930 --> 01:16:44,225
-Then where is it?
-"Where is it", indeed. Lost. Shh!

1112
01:16:44,350 --> 01:16:46,102
Perhaps.

1113
01:16:46,227 --> 01:16:48,729
Things do get lost, you know.

1114
01:16:48,854 --> 01:16:51,190
And now, you must excuse me.

1115
01:16:51,273 --> 01:16:54,527
Oh, you have a lot to do.

1116
01:16:54,610 --> 01:16:57,196
Do I?
Is that what I'm supposed to do now?

1117
01:16:57,279 --> 01:17:00,032
-Go looking for Gallifrey?
-That's entirely up to you.

1118
01:17:00,116 --> 01:17:03,536
Your choice, eh?
I can only tell you what I would do.

1119
01:17:03,619 --> 01:17:06,789
If I were you...
Oh, if I were you.

1120
01:17:06,914 --> 01:17:11,043
-(BOTH CHUCKLE)
-Perhaps I was you, of course.

1121
01:17:11,127 --> 01:17:14,421
Or perhaps you are me.

1122
01:17:14,547 --> 01:17:18,634
-(CHUCKLING) Congratulations.
-Thank you very much.

1123
01:17:18,759 --> 01:17:20,886
Or perhaps it doesn't matter
either way.

1124
01:17:22,429 --> 01:17:24,640
Who knows?

1125
01:17:24,765 --> 01:17:27,726
Who knows.

1126
01:17:43,325 --> 01:17:46,954
ELEVENTH DOCTOR: Clara sometimes
asks me if I dream.

1127
01:17:47,079 --> 01:17:49,582
"'Course I dream, " I tell her.

1128
01:17:49,665 --> 01:17:52,293
"Everybody dreams."”

1129
01:17:52,418 --> 01:17:55,296
"But what do you dream about?”
she'll ask.

1130
01:17:55,421 --> 01:17:58,340
"The same thing everybody
dreams about " I tell her.

1131
01:17:59,091 --> 01:18:01,677
"I dream about where I'm going.”

1132
01:18:01,760 --> 01:18:03,762
She always laughs at that.

1133
01:18:03,846 --> 01:18:07,016
"But you're not going anywhere.
You're just wandering about.”

1134
01:18:07,183 --> 01:18:09,101
That's not true.

1135
01:18:09,185 --> 01:18:11,645
Not any more.

1136
01:18:11,770 --> 01:18:14,190
I have a new destination.

1137
01:18:14,273 --> 01:18:17,860
My journey is the same as yours.
The same as anyone's.

1138
01:18:18,319 --> 01:18:21,322
It's taken me so many years,
so many lifetimes,

1139
01:18:21,447 --> 01:18:24,617
but at last, I know where I'm going.

1140
01:18:24,700 --> 01:18:27,119
Where I have always been going.

1141
01:18:28,204 --> 01:18:29,705
Home.

1142
01:18:29,788 --> 01:18:32,374
The long way round.

